<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="017" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>BFF unit + integration tests for FR-BFF-01..07</title>
    <phase>B: BFF resolver extension</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3-5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>016</dependencies>
    <blocks>018</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, testing, unit-test, integration-test</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include `testing` and `integration-test`. Test-creation task per task-execute rigor decision tree.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Must serialize after all Phase B impl tasks (010–016) so tests can target the completed integration.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Write unit + integration tests covering FR-BFF-01 through FR-BFF-07 plus NFR-02/05/08. Coverage: allow-list validation (valid/invalid/null/empty), ProblemDetails 400 shape (`INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED` with extension members), resolver fall-through to the existing 2-tier chain, DTO forward-compat (3 DTOs deserialize with/without `SearchIndexName`), end-to-end thread-through. Verify the existing BFF test suite passes UNMODIFIED (NFR-02).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    BFF test developer familiar with the existing `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` structure, xUnit conventions, and Spaarke testing patterns (see `.claude/patterns/testing/`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    All FR-BFF acceptance criteria are testable and tests pass. ProblemDetails schema validated. Forward-compat invariant proven by test (DTOs without `SearchIndexName` deserialize successfully). End-to-end integration test confirms the resolved index name surfaces in the issued Azure Search URL. Existing test suite passes UNMODIFIED.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase B implementation (tasks 010–016) is complete. This task locks in the behavior with tests so future refactors don't regress. The existing BFF test suite passing unmodified is the strongest backward-compat signal we have.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Models/Ai/</file>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/KnowledgeDeploymentService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md FR-BFF-01..07">Each FR has its own testable acceptance criterion; this task delivers the tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-02">Existing BFF test suite passes UNMODIFIED — pass count matches pre-change baseline.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-05">Performance — searches with explicit `searchIndexName` MUST be within 10% of today's baseline. Verified by perf test (10 runs each).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-08">ProblemDetails JSON schema validated for `400 INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED` (extension members present).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">Testing standards — xUnit + appropriate mocking (Moq or NSubstitute as already used in the project); Arrange/Act/Assert structure; descriptive test names.</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/testing.md">Spaarke testing conventions.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-testing-standards.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/unit-test-structure.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/mocking-patterns.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Unit test structure" location=".claude/patterns/testing/unit-test-structure.md">
        Arrange/Act/Assert; one assertion per logical concept; descriptive `MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedOutcome` test names.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="ProblemDetails schema test" location="ADR-019">
        Assert response status = 400; deserialize body as `ProblemDetails`; assert `type` contains `INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED`, `status` = 400, extension member naming rejected index.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Create or extend `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/KnowledgeDeploymentServiceTests.cs` with unit tests covering: (a) valid `indexName` returns bound `SearchClient`; (b) invalid `indexName` throws/returns `INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED`; (c) null `indexName` falls through to existing chain; (d) empty `indexName` falls through.</step>
    <step order="2">Add DTO forward-compat tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Models/Ai/` for all 3 DTOs: deserialize JSON WITHOUT `searchIndexName` and verify property is null + parse succeeds; deserialize JSON WITH `searchIndexName` and verify property is set.</step>
    <step order="3">Add ProblemDetails schema test for `400 INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED`: POST to endpoint with bad `searchIndexName`, assert status 400, deserialize body, assert `type`/`title`/`status`/`detail` + extension member naming the rejected index (NFR-08).</step>
    <step order="4">Add integration test for end-to-end thread-through: POST with valid `searchIndexName`, capture BFF log output, assert log includes the resolved index name in the issued Azure Search query URL (FR-BFF-07).</step>
    <step order="5">Add a performance smoke test (10 runs with explicit `searchIndexName`, 10 runs without) to verify NFR-05 (&lt; 10% delta). If a full perf harness doesn't exist, document the timing measurements in task notes rather than blocking on a new test framework.</step>
    <step order="6">Run the FULL existing BFF test suite (`dotnet test`); assert pass count matches the pre-Phase-B baseline. This is the NFR-02 gate. Update `TASK-INDEX.md` status: 🔲 → ✅; update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read existing test patterns</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create new test files</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Extend existing test files</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run `dotnet test`; capture pass counts</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/KnowledgeDeploymentServiceTests.cs (new or extended)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Models/Ai/*RequestTests.cs (3 DTOs)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/* (end-to-end + ProblemDetails schema)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">Perf measurements (10×10 runs) captured to task notes</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">FR-BFF-01..07: Each FR has at least one passing test covering its acceptance criterion.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NFR-02: Existing BFF test suite passes UNMODIFIED — `dotnet test` pass count matches pre-Phase-B baseline.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NFR-05: Searches with explicit `searchIndexName` within 10% of baseline (10×10 perf runs documented).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NFR-08: 400 INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED ProblemDetails schema validated by test.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The forward-compat DTO tests are the cheapest, highest-value tests in this task — they encode the backward-compat invariant directly. Prioritize them.

    If the integration-test harness in `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/` doesn't exist yet for this kind of end-to-end test, extending the unit-test layer with a `WebApplicationFactory`-based test is an acceptable fallback (still hits the full pipeline + DI).
  </notes>

